<h1>From Reese Meredith</h1>

<div class="docbody">

<p style="text-indent: 0;"><span style="float: left;">Esteemed Friend</span><span style="float: right;">Philadelphia May 5th 1773</span></p>     
<p style="clear: both; text-indent: 2em;">Colonel Washington</p> 
<p>From the little acquaintance I had with thee formerly, I take the liberty of recommending the Bearer Capt. John Harper who is in partnership with William HartshorneJohn Harper comes down in order to see the Country, if he likes it, they propose to come down and settle with you; they are Men that have a very pretty InterestWm Hartshorne lived with me some TimeThey are Industrious, Careful, Sober Men;<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0168-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0168-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> If Capt. Harper should want to draw on this place for Five hundred Pounds I will engage his Bills shall be paidAny Civilitys shewn him will be returnd by Thy Friend</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Reese Meredith</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-09-02-pb-0229">[229]</span>
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0168-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

   
   <p>Reese Meredith (17051777), the father of Samuel Meredith (1741<span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from '1787' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-07-07]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">1817</span>) whom GW appointed first treasurer of the United States, was a Quaker merchant in Philadelphia.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0168-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0168-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>John Harper (17281804) and William Hartshorne became prosperous merchants in Alexandria. GW had frequent dealings with them, particularly with Hartshorne after the war.</p>

</div>
</div>
